[{"location":"#PolyhedralCubature.jl-documentation","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","text":"This package allows to evaluate multiple integrals like","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","text":"int_-5^4int_-5^3-xint_-10^6-x-y f(x y z)textdztextdytextdx","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","text":"In other words, the domain of integration is given by a set of linear  inequalities:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","text":"leftbeginmatrix -5   leqslant  x  leqslant  4  -5   leqslant  y  leqslant  3-x  -10  leqslant  z  leqslant  6-x-y endmatrixright","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","text":"These linear inequalities define a convex polytope (in dimension 3, a  polyhedron).  In order to use the package, one has to get the matrix-vector representation  of these inequalities, of the form","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","text":"A (xyz) leqslant b","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","text":"The matrix A and the vector b appear when one rewrites the linear  inequalities above as:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","text":"leftbeginmatrix -x  leqslant  5  x  leqslant  4  -y  leqslant  5  x+y  leqslant  3  -z  leqslant  10  x+y+z  leqslant  6 endmatrixright","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","text":"The matrix A is given by the coefficients of x, y, z at the  left-hand sides, and the vector b is made of the upper bounds at the  right-hand sides:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","text":"A = [\n  -1  0  0;   # -x\n   1  0  0;   # x\n   0 -1  0;   # -y\n   1  1  0;   # x + y\n   0  0 -1;   # -z\n   1  1  1    # x + y + z\n]\nb = [5; 4; 5; 3; 10; 6]","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","text":"......","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","text":"___","category":"page"},{"location":"#Member-functions","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"Member functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","text":"Modules = [PolyhedralCubature]\nOrder   = [:type, :function]","category":"page"},{"location":"#PolyhedralCubature.integrateOnPolytope-Tuple{Function, Any, Any}","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.integrateOnPolytope","text":"integrateOnPolytope(f, A, b; dim, maxEvals, absError, tol, rule, info, fkwargs...)\n\nIntegration of a function over a convex polytope.\n\nArguments\n\nf: function to be integrated; must return a real scalar value or a real vector\nA: matrix corresponding to the coefficients of the variables in the linear inequalities\nb: vector made of the upper bounds of the linear inequalities\ndim: number of components of f\nmaxEvals: maximum number of calls to f\nabsError: requested absolute error\ntol: requested relative error\nrule: integration rule, an integer between 1 and 4; a 2*rule+1 degree integration rule is used\nfkwargs: keywords arguments of f\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#PolyhedralCubature.integratePolynomialOnPolytope-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"PolyhedralCubature.jl documentation","title":"PolyhedralCubature.integratePolynomialOnPolytope","text":"integratePolynomialOnPolytope(poly, A, b)\n\nExact integration of a polynomial over a convex polytope.\n\nArguments\n\npoly: typed polynomial\nA: matrix of the coefficients of the variables in the linear inequalities\nb: vector made of the upper bounds of the linear inequalities\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
